<TITLE> Janakantha editor, facing 48 years, out on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Jan20 (bdnews24.com) Janakantha editor Atiqullah Khan Masud, sentenced to over 48 years in separate graft cases, was released on bail at BSMMU Hospital on Tuesday. He was released from guard at his hospital cabin shortly after 6pm. Masud's wife Shamima A Khan, newly appointed Awami League whip Sagufta Yasmin Emili, BNP leader Ruhul Kuddus Talukder Dulu, Dhaka University professor Hossain Monsur among some hundred supporters greeted the editor as he came out. Masud waved to the crowd as he entered into a car which took him to the Janakhantha offices. The newspaper editor and businessman was arrested on Mar 7 2007 by joint forces. He was sentenced to 13 years by a special court on April 3 2008 in an illegal wealth case. He was sentenced the same year to another 35 years in five other cases involving falsifying of planning permission for construction. bdn
